{"word":"Samuel","slug":"samuel","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Samuel</b> <a href=\"#/H8050\">H8050</a> <br/> Miraculous birth of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=1&verse=20'>1Sa 1:20</a><br/> Consecrated to God before his birth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=1&verse=11'>1Sa 1:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=1&verse=22'>1Sa 1:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=1&verse=28'>1Sa 1:28</a><br/> His mother's song of thanksgiving<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=2&verse=10'>1Sa 2:10</a><br/> Ministered in the house of God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=2&verse=11'>1Sa 2:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=2&verse=19'>1Sa 2:19</a><br/> Blessed of God<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=2&verse=21'>1Sa 2:21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=3&verse=19'>1Sa 3:19</a><br/> His vision concerning the house of Eli<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=3&verse=18'>1Sa 3:18</a><br/> A prophet of the Israelites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=3&verse=21'>1Sa 3:21</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=4&verse=1'>1Sa 4:1</a><br/> A judge of Israel, his judgment seat at Beth-El, Gilgal, Mizpeh, and Ramah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=7&verse=17'>1Sa 7:17</a><br/> Organizes the tabernacle service<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=9&verse=22'>1Ch 9:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=26&verse=28'>1Ch 26:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=35&verse=18'>2Ch 35:18</a><br/> Israelites repent under his reproofs and admonitions<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=7&verse=6'>1Sa 7:6</a><br/> The Philistines defeated through his intercession and sacrifices<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=7&verse=14'>1Sa 7:14</a><br/> Makes his corrupt sons judges in Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=8&verse=3'>1Sa 8:3</a><br/> People desire a king; he protests<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=8&verse=22'>1Sa 8:22</a><br/> Anoints Saul king of Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=9'>1Sa 9</a><br/> Renews the kingdom of Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=11&verse=15'>1Sa 11:15</a><br/> Reproves Saul; foretells that his kingdom shall not be established<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=13&verse=15'>1Sa 13:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=15'>1Sa 15</a><br/> Anoints David to be king<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=16'>1Sa 16</a><br/> Shelters David when escaping from Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=19&verse=18'>1Sa 19:18</a><br/> Death of; the lament for him<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=25&verse=1'>1Sa 25:1</a><br/> Called up by the witch of En-Dor<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=28&verse=20'>1Sa 28:20</a><br/> His integrity as judge and ruler<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=12&verse=5'>1Sa 12:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=99&verse=6'>Psa 99:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=15&verse=1'>Jer 15:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=58&chapter=11&verse=32'>Heb 11:32</a><br/> Chronicles of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=29&verse=29'>1Ch 29:29</a><br/> Sons of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=6&verse=28'>1Ch 6:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=6&verse=33'>1Ch 6:33</a><br/> Called Shemuel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=6&verse=33'>1Ch 6:33</a>"}]}